# §§ self_authoring.csl — engine-self-authors-CSSL spec
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# § T11-W12-SELF-AUTHOR · Apocky-directive ‟teaching self coding and self authoring content”
# § canonical-impl : compiler-rs/crates/cssl-host-self-author/
# § sibling-impls  : cssl-host-coder-runtime · cssl-host-llm-bridge
#                  · cssl-substrate-sigma-runtime · cssl-substrate-sigma-chain
#
# § PRIME-DIRECTIVE
#   t∞: consent = OS · ¬ harm · ¬ surveillance · ¬ exfiltration
#   t∞: ¬ live-mutate-without-Σ-cap (EFFECT_WRITE bit REQUIRED)
#   t∞: ∀ attempts → Σ-Chain-anchor (immutable history)
#   t∞: sovereign-revoke-cap → cascading-rollback (revert-window)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§§ THESIS
  ⊢ engine 'd self-author CSSL ⊑ {scenes · NPC-lines · recipes · lore · systems}
  ⊢ flow : prompt → llm-bridge → CSSL-string → csslc-compile → sandbox-execute
            → quality-score → IF score ≥ θ ∧ cap-grant → live-mutate
            ELSE record-only
  ⊢ all-outcomes → TrainingPairLog → Σ-Chain-anchor
  ⊢ feedback-loop : KAN-loop (W12-3) reads-training-pairs → bias-adjust

§§ KIND.SET ≡ {Scene · NpcLine · Recipe · Lore · System}
  ⊢ Scene    : .cssl scene-file (entities · triggers · lighting · camera)
  ⊢ NpcLine  : single dialogue-snippet (composes-into-scene)
  ⊢ Recipe   : crafting recipe (in · out · station · time)
  ⊢ Lore     : prose-block (¬ executable · gated by Constraints.lore_only)
  ⊢ System   : rules+invariants+effects (high-impact · sovereign-bit-required)

§§ CONSTRAINTS
  ⌈max_lines⌉            ≤ 200 default · clamped per-request
  ⌈max_tokens⌉           ≤ 4096 default · LLM-budget
  ⌈forbid_effect_strings⌉ ⊇ {Effect::NetworkEgress · Effect::FsWrite · Effect::Surveil}
  ⌈lore_only⌉           Bool · IF true → kind W! Lore
  ⌈score_threshold⌉      0..100 · default 75 · ¬ auto-mutate-below

§§ FORBIDDEN.TARGETS ‼ structural-rejection-pre-LLM
  ⊢ compiler-rs/crates/csslc/        ← compiler-itself
  ⊢ compiler-rs/crates/cssl-rt/      ← runtime
  ⊢ compiler-rs/crates/cssl-substrate-* ← substrate-primitives (any)
  ⊢ compiler-rs/crates/cssl-host-coder-runtime/  ← cap-gate-itself
  ⊢ compiler-rs/crates/cssl-host-self-author/    ← bootstrap-loop-guard
  ⊢ compiler-rs/crates/cssl-host-attestation/    ← Σ-Chain-emitter
  ⊢ compiler-rs/crates/cssl-host-akashic-records/ ← audit-aggregator
  ⊢ compiler-rs/crates/cssl-host-sigma-chain/    ← chain-host
  ⊢ compiler-rs/crates/cssl-effects/             ← effect-system
  ⊢ compiler-rs/crates/cssl-caps/                ← cap-system
  ⊢ PRIME_DIRECTIVE.md
  ⊢ specs/grand-vision/

§§ SANDBOX.ISOLATION
  ⊢ ¬ network-egress     ← structurally · sandbox holds-no-socket-handle
  ⊢ ¬ FS-write-outside-scratch ← compile_only=true · no-codegen-no-link
  ⊢ ¬ subprocess-exec    ← caller-supplied CompileFn · in-process-only
  ⊢ deny_externs : src.contains("extern \"C\"") ⇒ Rejected
  ⊢ max_source_bytes : 64 KiB · oversize ⇒ Rejected
  ⊢ output : SandboxReport (in-memory) ← only channel

§§ SCORE.FORMULA  (compile + warning-free + tests + asserts)
  compile-Pass     ⇒ +40
  warnings == 0    ⇒ +20
  test_count > 0   ⇒ +20
  assert_count > 0 ⇒ +20
  forbidden-effect ⇒ score = 0  (override)
  compile-Fail     ⇒ score = 0  (override)
  ⟦score⟧ ∈ [0, 100]  · clamped

§§ LIVE-MUTATE.GATE  (Σ-cap REQUIRED)
  ⊢ pre-conditions ∀ (and-narrow) :
    ¬ forbidden-target    · target_path ∉ FORBIDDEN.TARGETS
    ¬ revoked-cap          · cap.holder_pubkey ∉ gate.revoked_set
    cap.preflight ✓        · sig-verify · ¬ expired · ¬ revocation_ref
    sandbox-Pass            · compile.Pass{}
    score ≥ threshold
    requires_sovereign ⇒ sovereign_bit_held
  ⊢ Allow ⇒ writer(target, cssl) ⇒ revert-window-arm
  ⊢ ∀ decisions (Allow + Deny) ⇒ Σ-Chain-anchor (kind = AttestationAnchor | CapRevoke)

§§ SIGMA-CHAIN.ANCHOR.SEQUENCE
  1. cap-grant  ⇒ EntryKind::CapGrant   payload=cap-spec
  2. mutate-attempt ⇒ EntryKind::AttestationAnchor payload=AnchorPayload-JSON
     {target_path · score · threshold · decision · source_blake3_hex}
  3. cap-revoke ⇒ EntryKind::CapRevoke  payload=holder_pubkey
  4. cascading-rollback ⇒ revert-window-trigger (cssl-host-coder-runtime)

§§ TRAINING-PAIR.LOG
  ⊢ ring-buffer · default-capacity 4096 · oldest-evicted-on-overflow
  ⊢ record-shape JSON :
    {ts_unix · prompt · kind · generated_cssl · source_blake3_hex
     · score · decision · target_path}
  ⊢ KAN-loop (W12-3) reads-training_log.iter() ⇒ gradient-descent-on-(prompt → CSSL → score)
  ⊢ feedback : score ≥ threshold = positive-signal · score < threshold = negative-signal

§§ FAILURE-MODES (¬ silent · ∀ recorded)
  ⊢ compile-error      ⇒ training-pair{score=0 · decision=NotAttempted}
  ⊢ sandbox-test-fail  ⇒ training-pair{score=low · decision=DenySandboxFailed}
  ⊢ cap-deny           ⇒ training-pair{decision=DenyCap{Invalid|Revoked|SovereignBitMissing}}
  ⊢ score-below-θ      ⇒ training-pair{decision=DenyScoreBelowThreshold}
  ⊢ forbidden-target   ⇒ early-reject-pre-LLM · ¬ training-pair (request-validation-fail)

§§ INTEGRATION.POINTS  (sibling-W12-fanout)
  ⊢ W12-1 cocreative.proposal_submit
    ⇒ orchestrator::submit_proposal(prompt · kind · ranked-candidates · target)
    ⇒ runs author() pipeline ⇒ training-pair recorded
  ⊢ W12-3 KAN-loop
    ⇒ reads orchestrator.training_log().iter() | as_slices()
    ⇒ gradient-descend on (prompt → CSSL → score) triples
    ⇒ updates KAN-substrate weights (writes-back are W12-3-private)
  ⊢ W12-4 ContentPackage (.ccpkg)
    ⇒ MAY consume training_log Allow-records as content-bundle inputs
    ⇒ promote-to-package via separate ccpkg-pipeline (¬ this slice)
  ⊢ W12-5+ UGC pipeline
    ⇒ user-submitted prompts route through orchestrator.author()
    ⇒ Mode-A LLM-bridge for richest output (cap-gated)

